09/02/2011
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- South African Archbishop Desmond Tutu and former Norwegian Prime Minister Gro Harlem Brundtland expressed confidence Tuesday (February 8th) that talks to reunify Cyprus can succeed despite difficulties. 
The two men, members of the so-called group of the Elders, a global peace initiative formed by Nelson Mandela, were in Nicosia to attend the launch of the film "Cyprus - Digging the past in search of the future". 
President Demetris Christofias and Turkish Cypriot leader Dervis Eroglu are to meet Wednesday as part of ongoing direct talks to reunify the divided island. 
(CNA, Famagusta Gazette - 08/02/11)
